  "text": "If ðW ; SÞ is a skew-angled Coxeter system and R is a fundamental set of reflections, then GðW ; SÞ is twist equivalent to GðW ; RÞ by Corollary A. It is therefore easy to determine all Coxeter systems ðW 0 ; S 0 Þ such that W 0 is isomorphic to W if we can guarantee that each fundamental set R in W consists of reflections. This motivates the definition of reflection-independence. Following [CITATION_1] we call a Coxeter group reflectionindependent if R J S W for any two fundamental sets S and R of W. Our next result provides an easy criterion to see whether a skew-angled Coxeter group is reflectionindependent. We call a vertex in a graph G an end-point if it is contained in precisely one edge; an edge is called a spike if it contains an endpoint.",
